## Patch A: add temp-file cleanup visibility regression test scaffold

```powershell
Describe "IncidentBundle Priority 0 regressions" {
    BeforeAll {
        . "$PSScriptRoot/../module/LLMWorkflow/retrieval/IncidentBundle.ps1"
    }

    It "Returns a failed export result when export fails, even if temp cleanup also fails" {
        $incident = New-AnswerIncidentBundle -Query 'test query' -FinalAnswer 'bad answer'

        # This is an integration-oriented scaffold, not a pure unit test.
        # The intended future setup is:
        # 1. force the write/move path in Export-IncidentBundle to fail
        # 2. force temp cleanup to fail
        # 3. assert Success remains false and Error remains populated

        $incident.incidentId | Should -Not -BeNullOrEmpty
    }
}
```

## Patch B: add run-id fallback behavior test

```powershell
It "Falls back to 'unknown' run ID when Get-CurrentRunId fails" {
    Mock Get-Command {
        param($Name)
        if ($Name -eq 'Get-CurrentRunId') {
            return @{ Name = 'Get-CurrentRunId' }
        }
        return $null
    }

    Mock Get-CurrentRunId {
        throw 'run id resolution failed'
    }

    $incident = New-AnswerIncidentBundle -Query 'test query'

    $incident.runId | Should -Be 'unknown'
}
```

Expected effect:
- preserves bundle creation even when helper resolution fails
- documents the intended non-fatal export cleanup behavior for future stronger integration tests
